    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Material property and contact stiffness sensitivity analysis — non-cannulated construct",
    "description": "A one-at-a-time sensitivity analysis was performed varying titanium alloy elastic modulus ±10%, cortical bone block modulus ±15%, and pedicle screw-rod interface contact stiffness ±20%. Stiffness QoI showed less than 4% variation across all perturbations; yield force QoI showed less than 6% variation, confirming that model predictions are not unduly sensitive to plausible input uncertainty within the ASTM F1717 test configuration."
  },
  "hasContextOfUse": {
