      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (Lab A: n=6, Lab B: n=5). All specimens from the same production lot with dimensional inspection confirming conformance to nominal geometry (Cpk > 1.33 for all critical dimensions). Inter-laboratory coefficient of variation for stiffness = 4.5%, within acceptable range for ASTM F1717. Sample size justification documented: N=11 provides 80% power to detect a 10% difference in mean stiffness at α = 0.05. Gradation 2 achieved: statistically justified sample size with dimensional inspection and inter-laboratory consistency.",
